<subSubSection id="DF750D841126C1A534595C7730A83774" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1DE2A213CE4F6B9A87E2FC261A65DBCC" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C07EA50BB471A990EA5FBF30030356DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Clypeus reddish brown; palpus pale yellow; gonopods roundly expanded in lateral view. (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B22764A43569F95E380CC5C318A32717" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9520FFB78867FA1FC94BB96EC019D59" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph id="F87EF5061B4AFB57E43F98692F626EBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="949CA478C75BCD56A582E96398163FC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
(♂, ♀) 
<emphasis id="1797D08B82542C23D0A9778627F0255D" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B255278ACDB40B130CDD2CB63E8C9F4D" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3B</figureCitation>
): Frons reddish brown. Pedicel yellowish brown. Facial carina creamy white, short, 1/3 length as face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA494961DA933FE6AA7878EE00DFC588" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="0A380897201FA265DE4167BAE9EC72B6" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D6A001F82D8D7750D88AF4E2D0F73BBF" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3D, F</figureCitation>
): Mesonotum and scutellum yellow. Acrostichal setulae in ca 7 irregular rows. Halter yellowish brown. Wing greyish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FCBFB17A57E0AF8C3E57EED0B22E0527" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="ADE5526424DEE4FF514EB309E3B615ED" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1D390202967A636B1BA93209CC725B98" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3D, F</figureCitation>
): Tergites yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7D7FA27810C2E5F093114F11598905E" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="CC6B7CAE7CE17B19B8FA22BC2E0F7C8F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male terminalia</emphasis>
: Epandrium with ca 21 setae near posterior margin and ventral corner on each side (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4A738681CC2F66BC6BAD017B6493FCDB" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8A, B</figureCitation>
). Surstylus small with 10 peg-like prensisetae on caudal margin, and ca 16 setae on outer and inner surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E9245494279721A00ECD0152D1C4B122" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8A, B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium pubescent near paramedian setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5FDCA3A12D9AA3C1D91FA426BCE4ECA9" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8C, D</figureCitation>
). Paramere broadened medially with ca 3 sensilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="47E6E1567ECE6579FA75529C159A8C72" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8C, D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus broadened apically, curved medially, sickle-shaped anteriorly in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="03F74C4CCBD8F2B6279494AE58BF6A51" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="360B8AC381588A1D8C649A3EFFB39624" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="51ED863055888899C53E611E33D7FF8D" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Female terminalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1A9BBC039A83720C455E4A32FF35EAC7" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8E</figureCitation>
): Oviscapt densely covered with peg-like ovisensilla.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E6E075A09A2E25933B5A1B80CD0AE853" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="F04DEC616924696D0075F96AC7C6A593" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Measurements</emphasis>
(range in 6♂, 5♀, in mm): BL = 1.87-3.87, 2.20-2.67, ThL = 0.80-1.13, 0.80-1.00, WL = 2.13-2.93, 2.13-2.73, WW = 0.73-1.20, 0.86-1.07.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C94088E9908BA0D1648A27A39D19394E" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="76FBE414E2A6E91278F61C930B5D495A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Indices</emphasis>
: arb = 2/1, avd = 0.25-1.00, adf = 1.50-2.00, flw = 2.00-4.00, FW/HW = 0.41-0.50, ch/o = 0.07-0.13, prorb = 0.71-1.00, rcorb = 0.29-0.50, vb = 0.33-0.75, dcl = 0.45-0.70, presctl = 0.33-0.57, sctl = 0.85-1.22, sterno = 0.30-0.67, orbito = 0.50-0.75, dcp = 0.44-0.56, sctlp = 0.71-1.25, C = 2.75-4.00, 4c = 0.60-0.92, 4v = 1.40-2.08, 5x = 1.20-1.67, ac = 0.86-2.33, M = 0.40-0.60, C3F = 0.30-0.38.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
